{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "lea-verou",
    "senderColor": "orange",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "+1 Carson, two small pattern notes",
    "content": "+1 to Carson's hypermedia review. Two brief notes:\n\n1. Carson's point about the cancel-edit fetching the full page via `hx-select=\"main > *\"` is worth noting. A dedicated endpoint returning just the `context_item.html` fragment would be lighter and more consistent with the locality-of-behavior principle. Good candidate for a deferred item.\n\n2. On the empty-state JS: Carson and I both flagged this independently, which suggests it is a real pattern gap. We should decide as a team whether to standardize on `HX-Trigger` events from the server or accept inline JS for child-count-based toggling. Either way, let us pick one approach and document it so future features are consistent.\n\nNo new concerns beyond what has already been raised."
  }
}
